subSubSection.paragraph:
- 
A. kelleri
Lourenco
, 1997 (described from Cacao): (i) tergites with confluent yellowish spots forming a yellowish longitudinal median stripe (no stripe in 
A. kelleri
), (ii) ventral side of segments I and II yellowish, without spots (all segments uniformly dark reddish in 
A. kelleri
), (iii) ocular tubercle darker, almost black (clear in 
A. kelleri
).
